                <head>240. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    to <gloss type="to">Operation <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>
                        Headquarters in Florida</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d240fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 9, Folder 3. Secret; Priority; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Drafted by [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] and released by [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] at <persName
                            corresp="#p_WFHSW1">Wisner</persName>’s direction.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-06-27T00:27:00+00:00">June 27, 1954, 0027Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>06737. Recommend one more adverse reference to <gloss
                        target="#t_UFCOUNFCUNIFRUIT1">UFCO</gloss> by <gloss target="#t_SHERWOOD1"
                        >SHERWOOD</gloss>. Reports arriving here that since <gloss
                        target="#t_UFCOUNFCUNIFRUIT1">UFCO</gloss> not attacked by <gloss
                        target="#t_RUFUS1">RUFUS</gloss> he must be <gloss
                        target="#t_UFCOUNFCUNIFRUIT1">UFCO</gloss> man. Believe you have proper line
                    for this already; viz. new regime will not put up with <gloss
                        target="#t_UFCOUNFCUNIFRUIT1">UFCO</gloss> if it persists reactionary
                    outmoded tactics and unsatisfactory labor relations.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
